UNITED STATES ex rel. George CATINO, Appellant, v. Wm. P. McDERMITT, United States Marshal for the District of New Jersey, Appellee.* No. 6706. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit Jan. 13, 1939. Max Mehler and F. M. P. Pearse, both of Newark, N. J., for appellant. Hubert J. Harrington, of Newark, N. J., for appellee.

Before DAVIS, BIGGS, and MARIS, Circuit Judges.

Rehearing denied March 2, 1939.

 PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed for want of jurisdiction upon the authority of Hartmann v. Sloan, 3 Cir., 99 F.2d 942.
